        <abstract> 
<p><hi rend="italic">Mimosa</hi> too far gone to send now.</p>  
<p>CD’s marjoram is the common [<hi rend="italic">Origanum</hi>] <hi rend="italic">vulgare</hi>, not the pot herb.</p> 
            <p>On the water injury, Thiselton-Dyer and he may have used too fine a spray, but plant is insensitive.</p> 
<p>Horribly angry at P. G. Tait’s letter in <hi rend="italic">Nature</hi> [8 (1873): 381–2].</p>  
<p>Tyndall writes that he is strong – the next number of <hi rend="italic">Nature</hi> will prove it.</p> 
            <p>G. Henslow is much better.</p>
            <p>JDH leaves for Bradford [BAAS meeting] tomorrow.</p> 
<p>Rejoices at CD’s success with <hi rend="italic">Drosera</hi>; longs to be at <hi rend="italic">Nepenthes</hi>.</p> 
        </abstract>
